Boil a full #kettle{}.

Meanwhile, halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips.

Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/2%tsp} on high heat.

Add the @penne pasta{180%g} and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with @oil{1%tbsp} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{1%tbsp} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @diced British chicken thigh{260%g} and sliced pepper. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Fry until the chicken is cooked through and the pepper has softened, ~{8-10%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

While everything cooks, peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%g}.

When the chicken and veg have 1 min of cooking time left, add the garlic to the pan and fry until fragrant.

Add the @tomato passata{1%carton}, @chicken stock paste{10%g}, @chipotle paste{20%g} (add less if you'd prefer things milder), @sugar{1%tsp} and @water{50%ml} for the sauce (see pantry for both amounts) to the pan.

Stir and bring to the boil, then reduce the heat and simmer until slightly thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir through the @BBQ sauce{48%g}, cooked pasta and @butter{20%g} (see pantry for amount). Heat until the pasta is piping hot and the butter has melted, ~{1%minute}.

Share the BBQ chicken pasta between your #serving bowls{}.

Sprinkle over the cheese. Enjoy!